FBIS4-47905 "drafr087_a_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda RPF Urges Tanzania To Cooperate With UN RPF Urges Tanzania To Cooperate With UN EA0405162094 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to Rwanda 1100 GMT 4 May 94 EA0405162094 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura English BFN [Excerpts] The UN Human Rights Commission is planning to send a team to Rwanda to investigate human rights abuses in Rwanda. The UNHCR should also investigate well-known criminals who have fled the country. A number of them have fled to Tanzania and they have been identified by many, including the UNHCR officials in Tanzania. [passage omitted] The Tanzanian Government should cooperate with the United Nations and bring these criminals to justice. This is what Rwanda needs urgently. [passage omitted]
